org.apache.geode.cache

Interface RegionEvent<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CacheEvent<K,V>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    RoleEvent<K,V>

    public interface RegionEvent<K,V>
extends CacheEvent<K,V>
    Contains information about an event affecting a region, including its identity and the circumstances of the event. This is passed in to CacheListener and CacheWriter.
    Since:
    GemFire 2.0
    See Also:
    CacheListener, CacheWriter, EntryEvent

      • isReinitializing

        boolean isReinitializing()
        Return true if this region was destroyed but is being reinitialized, for example if a snapshot was just loaded. Can only return true for an event related to region destruction.
